  <compounddef id="SHR" kind="page">
    <compoundname>SHR</compoundname>
    <title>SHR Function</title>
    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">SHR(value,<sp/>count)</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Performs a <bold>bitwise shift right</bold> operation on an integer. The first parameter is the value to shift, the second is the number of bit positions.</para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<sect3 id="SHR_1autotoc_md385">
<title>Examples</title>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">PRINT<sp/>SHR(4,<sp/>1)</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Produces <computeroutput>2</computeroutput> (<computeroutput>0100</computeroutput> → <computeroutput>0010</computeroutput>).</para>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">PRINT<sp/>SHR(9,<sp/>2)</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Produces <computeroutput>2</computeroutput> (<computeroutput>1001</computeroutput> → <computeroutput>0010</computeroutput>, fractional part discarded).</para>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">REM<sp/>Divide<sp/>by<sp/>powers<sp/>of<sp/>two<sp/>using<sp/>SHR</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">n<sp/>=<sp/>40</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">PRINT<sp/>SHR(n,<sp/>3)<sp/><sp/><sp/>&apos;<sp/>Same<sp/>as<sp/>40<sp/>/<sp/>8<sp/>=<sp/>5</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
</sect3>
<sect3 id="SHR_1autotoc_md387">
<title>Notes</title>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Operates on 64-bit integers.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Shifting right by <computeroutput>n</computeroutput> positions is equivalent to integer division by <computeroutput>2^n</computeroutput>.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Bits shifted out on the right are discarded; new bits on the left are filled with zero.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>This is a <bold>logical shift</bold> (fills with zero), not an arithmetic shift. Negative values are not sign-extended.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>If the shift count is negative or larger than the bit width, behaviour is undefined.</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
